The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Friday, January 16, 2004 				 Bail for Jogi
																								New Delhi, Jan. 15: A Delhi court today granted bail to former Chhattisgarh chief minister Ajit Jogi in a case of allegedly using forged documents to tarnish the image of the Intelligence Bureau and the Centre, reports our special correspondent.																								Jogi, who was granted bail on a personal bond and surety of Rs 10,000 each, said he had trust in the court, but refused to comment on the chargesheet. 																								February 24 has been fixed for the next hearing.
